The paper discusses the use of computational models to understand the evolution of human creativity, which suggests that it is likely to fall under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks to model cultural evolution also suggests that it could be classified under Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of computational models to test hypotheses, which could fall under the category of Computational Complexity (cs.CC). The use of simulations to test the impact of different factors on creativity suggests that it could also be classified under Simulation and Modeling (cs.SD). Finally, the use of computational models to understand the evolution of human behavior suggests that it could be classified under Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
